Defines a rule for inferring geospatial air quality contexts. The rule defines the geocoding method to obtain a users address at the current location, and the buffering method to retrieve the locations of nearby hospitals.
Geospatial air quality context information model

Defines a rule for inferring geospatial air quality contexts from a user's location and nearby air quality monitoring stations. The rule includes geospatial operations to identify and obtain air quality data from nearby air quality monitoring stations. Interpolation methods such as Kriging and Inverse Distance Weighting (IDW) are then applied to infer the air quality data at the users current location.

UML:Diagram.name: Fig 6. Locational Air Quality Context Information Model

UML:TaggedValue.value: The locational air quality context information model is designed for the users who use AQMA(Air Quality Mobile Application), the air quality monitoring stations that provide air quality data to AQODP(Air Quality Open Data Platform), and the air quality event detected from AQSDP (Air Quality Social Data Platform). These classes are associated to retrieve and infer locational contexts from users, air quality monitoring stations, and air quality events.
